This paper proposes a distributed reinforcement learning method for multi-agent systems, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves coordination and consensus among multiple agents, which falls under the sub-categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses a resource allocation example, which is a common application in the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
